<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="187" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[153,1436,151,247]" pageId="18" pageNumber="187">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,306,188,212]" pageId="18" pageNumber="187">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species can be easily distinguished from its congeners by the following characters: large body size, substraight lateral margin of pronotum, sternite IX, tergite X and aedeagus.
</paragraph>
